headline: 3 Reasons to Sell CVS and 1 Stock to Buy Instead
summary: Over the past six months, CVS Health has been a great trade, beating the S&P 500 by 13.8%. Its stock price has climbed to $65.46, representing a healthy 19% increase. This was partly thanks to its solid quarterly results, and the run-up might have investors contemplating their next move.
